Chaos engineering is the practice of intentionally introducing controlled failures or disruptions into a system to test its resilience, identify weaknesses, and ensure that it can withstand unexpected failures. Chaos engineering aims to uncover vulnerabilities before they impact users in production environments.

Tools: Gremlin, Chaos Mesh, LitmusChaos, and Pumba

